<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="676" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Gummeré</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-07-29"><hi rend="italic">July 29,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Referring to your No. 25, you will advise minister for foreign affairs
                            that the Government of the United States will take part in the proposed
                            conference and will announce its representatives when time and place of
                            meeting are determined.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Adee.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>